Senate Bill 90
AMENDM ENT 90A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Nelson
1 An Act to expand the information required to be sent to the prescription drug
2 monitoring program for each registry identification card holder.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 34-20G-88.1 be AMENDED:
5 34-20G-88.1. TheFor each cardholder and nonresident cardholder, the
6 department shall submit the name and date of birth of a qualifying patient who receives
7 a registry identification card to the prescription drug monitoring program, authorized
8 pursuant to chapter 34-20E, the cardholder's:
9 (1) Name;
10 (2) Physical address, except that if the applicant is homeless, no address is required;
11 (3) Date of birth;
12 (4) Gender; and
13 (5)(4) Registry identification card number.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

